Rules of index notation: \begin{itemize} \item Sum over all repeated indices. \item Increment all unique indices fully at least once, covering all combinations. \item Increment repeated indices first. \item A comma indicates differentiation, with respect to coordinate $x_i$ \item The number of non-repeated indices indicates the order of the tensor result of a tensor multiplication or derivative. \end{itemize}

