$$

\frac{l^{2}}{l_{0}^{2}} = \mathbf{m} \cdot \mathbf{C} \cdot \mathbf{m}\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\frac{l_{0}^{2}}{l^{2}} = \mathbf{n} \cdot \mathbf{B}^{- 1} \cdot \mathbf{n}$$

{The definitions of these quantities are}

{ The Right Stretch Tensor $$

\mathbf{U = \mathbf{C}^{1/2} = \left( {\mathbf{F}^{T} \cdot \mathbf{F}} \right)^{1/2}\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\, U_{ij} = C_{ij}^{1/2}$$

